        "description": "Conduct a Visa Entitlement Check for a specified Visa Holder.\n\nYour organisation may be authorised to see one or more categories of Visa Entitlement data.\nThese categories are nominated during enrolment and determine which scopes are present in your OAuth access tokens.\n\nBelow is a list Entitlement Categories and the corresponding scopes required to request that category.\n\n* IMMIGRATION_STATUS: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:G\n* LEGAL_PRACTITIONER: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:A\n* LICENSING_ELIGIBILITY: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:L\n* MEDICARE_ELIGIBILITY: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:M\n* REGISTERED_MIGRATION_AGENT: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:I\n* RESIDENCE_STATUS: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:C\n* STUDY_ENTITLEMENTS: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:D\n* WORK_ENTITLEMENTS: VSA:ENT:R VSA:ENT:E\n\nRequests for categories for which you have not been authorised for will result in errors.\n\nAll authorised organisations have access to the following common fields:\n\nEach Entitlement Category returns additional data specific to that category.\nOrganisations authorised to access more than one Entitlement Category must make multiple requests to see all data.\n",
